  "texts": [
    "LoRA resultsWhile full-size SFT can lead to sizable improvements, it is often resourceintensive.",
    "This quickly becomes prohibitive for large models that go beyond 70B parameters.",
    "In contrast, LoRA offers a more efficient alternative by finetuning only a small subset of parameters, significantly reducing the required VRAM, e.g.",
    "full-size SFT for the 70B Llama model usually needs more than a single node of eight H100 80GB GPUs, while the LoRA version can reduce the GPU requirements to around four H100 80GB GPUs.",
    "This makes LoRA appealing for scenarios with limited GPU resources."
  ],
